  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Sparse Solvers in the Accelerate framework handle the solution of systems of equations where the coefficient matrix is sparse, that is, most of the entries in the matrix are zero."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Many problems in science and technology require the solution of large systems of simultaneous equations. When these equations are linear, they are normally represented as the matrix equation "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ax = b"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (and even when the equations are nonlinear, the problem is often solved as a sequence of linear approximations)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2904627",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2904627",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "WWDC 2017 - Session 711 (Accelerate and Sparse Solvers)",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/711/"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Solution Approaches Offered by Accelerate",
          "anchor": "2882595"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Accelerate offers two different solution approaches:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Direct methods"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " perform a factorization such as Cholesky ("
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "emphasis",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "A = LLᵀ"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ") or QR. These methods provide a fast and accurate black-box solution."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Iterative methods"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " find an approximate solution requiring only repeated multiplication by "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "emphasis",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "A"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " or "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "emphasis",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Aᵀ"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ". Although they require less memory than direct methods, and can be faster for very large problems, they typically require problem-specific preconditioners to be effective. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Just as Sparse "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/blas"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " provides a sparse counterpart to dense BLAS, Sparse Solvers in the Accelerate framework provide a sparse counterpart to the dense factorizations provided by LAPACK."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Sparse Matrices",
          "anchor": "2882598"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In the simplest case, a matrix "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is stored as a 2D dense array of floating point values, and routines from BLAS, LAPACK, and other similar libraries are used to manipulate matrices and solve equations. However, such algorithms normally require "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "O(n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "²"
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ")"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " data and "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "O(n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "³"
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ")"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " operations and, as a result, scaling to a large "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is prohibitive."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The key to avoiding the expense of these algorithms is taking advantage of the fact that in many real-world applications, most of the entries in "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " are zero. Such matrices are said to be "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "sparse"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (conversely, nonsparse matrices are called "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "dense"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "). "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "These zeros arise naturally in these types of situations:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Incomplete data sets"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " (for example, each user buys only a small fraction of the products from a retailer)"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Limited connectivity"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " (for example, most people on social networks are connected only to a tiny proportion of the entire user base)"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Physical properties"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " (for example, points on structural meshes only connect to locally adjacent points)."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By exploiting these zero entries, you can often reduce the storage and computational requirements to "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "O(tau*n)"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "O(tau*n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "²"
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ")"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " respectively, where "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "tau"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is the average number of entries in each column. This reduction makes the solution of large problems ("
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in the millions or larger) tractable on most computers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For example, the sparse benchmark matrix "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ldoor"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which arises from structural modeling, has 952,200 x 952,200 entries with an average of 25 nonzero "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/double"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " entries per column. "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/sparse_solvers#2882599"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " shows the number of floating point operations (1 Tflop is 10¹² floating point operations) and the memory required to perform Cholesky factorization on that matrix."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "header": "both",
          "rows": [
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": []
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Floating point operations"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Memory"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Dense"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "287,782 Tflop"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "6,800 GB"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Sparse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "0.0783 Tflop"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "1.2 GB"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
